========,1,preface.
Orrville is a city in Wayne County, Ohio, United States.
It is about 20 miles southwest of Akron.
The population was 8,380 at the 2010 census.
The J.M.
Smucker Co., owner of the Smucker's brand, is headquartered in Orrville.
========,2,History.
Orrville was laid out in 1852, and named after Judge Smith Orr, proprietor.
A post office called Orrville has been in operation since 1852.
